  "prompt": "WhatsApp is the difference between hard wood and soft wood?",
  "response": "Here are the key differences between hardwood and softwood:\n\nHardwood:\n1. Comes from deciduous trees (trees that lose leaves seasonally)\n2. Generally denser and more complex wood structure\n3. Slower growing trees\n4. Usually more expensive\n5. Examples: oak, maple, walnut, mahogany\n6. Often used for furniture, flooring, and high-quality woodworking\n7. Typically harder and more durable\n\nSoftwood:\n1. Comes from coniferous trees (evergreen trees with needles)\n2. Less dense wood structure\n3. Faster growing trees\n4. Generally less expensive\n5. Examples: pine, spruce, cedar, fir\n6. Often used for construction, paper production, and general carpentry\n7. Usually softer and less dense\n\nThe terms \"hardwood\" and \"softwood\" refer to the botanical classification of trees, not necessarily the physical hardness of the wood. Some softwoods can be harder than some hardwoods.\n\nMain differences are in their origin, density, growth rate, cost, and typical uses.",
